As crowds rushed over to the scene, the man in question is seen placing his foot over the phone.

He then slowly reached down, picked it up, and put it in his pocket, before walking down to another part of the station.

Police tell NECN that the still unidentified 26-year-old male suspect from Brockton, Mass., turned himself in at the MBTA Police Headquarters Friday night. 

MBTA Transit Police had released images from the video in a bid to track down the alleged thief. 

